Step 1: Create a bootable Window 10.... USB
Step 2: Open Repair a system 
Step 3: Open Comand Prompt
Step 4: type c:
Step 5: cd windows
Step 6: cd system32
Step 7: ren utilman.exe utilman_bak.exe   //Rename utilman to utilma_bak
Step 8: copy cmd.exe utilman.exe  //To make a copy of the cmd.exe file named utilman.exe
Step 9: exit
Step 10: Open control panel by clicking on Accessibility option in lock screen
Step 11: control userpasswords2    // For doing things with GUI   // Not prefer
Step 12: net user   //for showing user name
Step 13: net user "name of user without quote marks" *
Step 14: type new password 
Step 15: type new password again

Done !!  ---->>>>>> You changed your Password not PIN


